Sentencas: Double-layered oxygen electrode consisting of La0.65Sr0.35MnO3 (LSM) and La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.2Co0.8O3-delta (LSCF) top layer was prepared and evaluated in the present work.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.65Sr0.35MnO3-based double-layered oxygen electrode for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: As compared with the single-layered LSM electrode, the polarization resistance of the double-layered LSM-LSCF electrode decreased by 2.9 times at 800 degrees C and the polarization overpotential decreased by 3.4 times.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.65Sr0.35MnO3-based double-layered oxygen electrode for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance was further reduced by more than 3 times through Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) infiltration.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.65Sr0.35MnO3-based double-layered oxygen electrode for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The solid oxide fuel cell with SDC infiltrated LSM-LSCF oxygen electrode exhibited a maximum power density of 671 mW.cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, 5 times higher than that of the LSM-based cell.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.65Sr0.35MnO3-based double-layered oxygen electrode for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: The hydrogen production rate of the electrolysis cell was 547.58 mL.cm(-2).h(-1) under 1.5 V at 800 degrees C, about 3 times as that of LSM oxygen electrode (186.01 mL.cm(-2).h(-1)).
Titulo: Characterization of La0.65Sr0.35MnO3-based double-layered oxygen electrode for reversible solid oxide cells

Sentencas: Both the fuel cell and electrolysis cell properties were dramatically improved, demonstrated an enhanced reaction process for LSM oxygen electrode.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.65Sr0.35MnO3-based double-layered oxygen electrode for reversible solid oxide cells
